 Hollywood Boulevard; he and Tex Ritter were the first father-and-son pair to be so honored in different categories.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book| last1=Yasbeck| first1=Amy| title=With Love and Laughter, John Ritter| year=2010| isbn=978-1-4165-9841-1| url-access=registration| url=https://archive.org/details/withlovelaughter00yasb| publisher=Gallery Books| location=New York}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Biography|California|Film|Television}}\n{{Commons|John Ritter}}\n* {{iMDb name|0000615}}\n* {{tcmdb name|id=162269|name=John Ritter}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* [http://www.emmys.com/celebrities/john-ritter John Ritter at Emmys.com]\n* [http://www.famously-dead.com/movies/john-ritter.html Famously Dead]\n* [http://johnritterfoundation.org/ John Ritter Foundation]\n* [http://columbiasurgery.org/news/2015/08/24/john-ritter-s-life-saving-rules \"Ritter Rules\"]\n* [http://www.johnritterresearchprogram.org/ John Ritter Research Program in Aortic and Vascular Diseases]\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for John Ritter\n|list =\n{{EmmyAward ComedyLeadActor 1976-2000}}\n{{GoldenGlobeBestActorTVComedy 1970-1989}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ritter, John}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:2003 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American male comedians]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male stage actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American male comedy actors]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Best Musical or Comedy Actor Golden Globe (television) winners]]\n[[Category:Burials at Forest Lawn Memorial Park (Hollywood Hills)]]\n[[Category:Comedians from California]]\n[[Category:Contestants on American game shows]]\n[[Category:Deaths from aortic dissection]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Burbank, California]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Outstanding Performance by a Lead Actor in a Comedy Series Primetime Emmy Award winners]]\n[[Category:USC School of Dramatic Arts alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:Theatre World Award winners]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTelevision", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Ritter"}
{"title_page": "Raymond Ebanks", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Raymond Ebanks\n| birth name          = Raymond Anthony Ebanks\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1970|1|2|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[London]], [[England]]<ref>England and Wales Birth Registration Index, 1837-2008</ref>\n| image               =\n| caption             = Raymond Ebanks in 2012 (Ebanks, Darude, Max'C, Orkidea, Js16)\n| image_size          = \n| background          = solo_singer\n| alias               = B.O. Dubb, B.O.W.\n| origin              = \n| genre               = [[Electronica]], [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n| years_active        = 1994-2006; 2011\n| label               = \n| associated_acts     = [[Bomfunk MC's]], Soup De loop, [[Beats And Styles]], Kollabo Brothers\n| website             = \n}}\n\n'''Raymond Anthony Ebanks''', aka '''B.O. Dubb''' (formerly known as B.O.W.; born 2 January 1970) is a semi-retired [[Finland|Finnish]] [[rap music|rapper]] best known as the frontman of the hip-hop group the [[Bomfunk MC's]].\n\n== Early career ==\n\nRaymond was born in [[London]] to a [[Jamaica]]n-[[England|English]] father and a Finnish mother. He began recording music as a teenager in the early 90s as part of the hip hop group \"The Master Brothers\", who often performed over DJ sets at clubs. Whilst no recordings were made, some of their performances were recorded, and have emerged online. Around this time, Raymond performed guest raps on the song Cryin' Out by Rama (1994).\n\n== Soup De Loop ==\n\nIn 1995, Raymond teamed up with longtime producer Jaakko \"[[JS16]]\" Salovaara and singer Mari Vesala to form the pop group Soup De Loop, and signed to the now defunct Blue Bubble Records. Their music was a combination of female sung house and G-Funk hip hop music, with Mari singing and Raymond providing raps. The group released an album, \"Brainspotting\" in 1997, as well as several singles including \"Keep On Doing\", which was a hit in Finland and appeared on several dance compilations around the time. Despite this, the group didn't have any success outside Finland. Mari left the group some time after the album was released, and they broke up rather than look for another singer.\n\n== Bomfunk MCs - 1999-2005 ==\n\nAfter the breakup of Soup De Loop, Ebanks and Salovaara teamed up with DJ Ismo \"DJ Gismo\" Lappalainen to form Bomfunk MCs. The band were signed to Sony Music Finland due to Blue Bubble Records going down under. The band quickly became known for the breakdancing in their videos and the graffiti in their album cover designs, both things which contributed to their popularity. Despite the associations with breakdancing, the band did perform slower paced hip hop songs as well and some more trancey material later on. The group released two albums with DJ Gismo - [[In Stereo (Bomfunk MC's album)|In Stereo]] and [[Burnin' Sneakers]], and released a number of successful singles, the most notable of which being [[Uprocking Beats]] and [[Freestyler (song)|Freestyler]]. Freestyler in particular became the band's signature song, which they are still remembered for to this day.\n\nThe band remained popular in Finland and Europe, but lost popularity elsewhere and their last release in the UK was \"Super Electric\", whose parent album, [[Burnin' Sneakers]] was never released in the UK due to poor sales of the single. However, the band contributed the official World Cup 2002 song for Sweden \"[[I Know There's Something Going On|(Crack It) Something Goin' On]]\", as well as contributed \"Put Your Hands Up\" and \"We R Atomic\" to the PlayStation game [[Firebugs (video game)|Firebugs]], in which they appeared as playable characters. These appearances revived the band's popularity in the UK, but it wasn't enough for the album to be released there. DJ Gismo left Bomfunk MCs in 2002 in order to join the group Stonedeep. He was replaced by Skillsters duo, which consists of Riku Pentti (DJ) and Okke Komulainen (keyboards).\n\nIn 2004, Salovaara guested on a number of songs by [[Beats And Styles]]. These have been erroneously credited as Bomfunk MC's songs, although the only real difference is the producer.\n\nIn 2005, the group signed to Universal/Polydor and recorded the album \"Reverse Psychology\". This album was very different to the previous two, as it had far more of a straightforward hip hop sound, in that respect, more in common with the \"Soup De Loop\" material. The album was half produced by Salovaara, and the other half by Pentti and Komulainen. The band also experimented more with trance inspired songs such as \"Hypnotic\" and \"Turn It Up\", and dance-rock songs such as \"No Way In Hell\" and \"Reverse Psychology\". The album also featured a guest appearance from [[Kurtis Blow]], of [[The Breaks (Kurtis Blow song)|The Breaks]] fame. Whilst the album produced the big European hit \"No Way In Hell\", it quickly became rare and obscure, due to only being released in Scandinavia, Germany and Eastern Europe. DJ Gismo appears on the cover of the album despite not contributing to it, this is likely to be for marketing reasons.\n\nA while after the release of the album, the group quietly split up. It has said this was due to Ebanks desire to retire from the spotlight. Salovaara has continued producing music.\n\n== Post-Bomfunk MCs ==\n\nSince Bomfunk MC's breakup, Ebanks has largely disappeared from the music industry, although he did guest on a few tracks.\n\nIn 2011 a Finnish rap compilation \"{{lang|fi|Rappiotaidetta: Suomir\u00e4pin Vaippaik\u00e4}}\" was released, which features Ebanks performing a song entitled \"{{lang|fi|Keijo Ei Pelaa}}\" under the pseudonym Keijo K from 1990. It is possibly the only released recording of Ebanks rapping in Finnish.\n\nIn 2014 Soup De Loop's album Brainspotting appeared for digital download worldwide, after being an out of print and expensive Finland-only release for years. The masters were owned by Sony-BMG who had taken over the Blue Bubble Label on which the album was originally released.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===with Soup De Loop===\n\n===Albums===\n\"Brainspotting\" (1997)\n\n===Singles===\n*\"Keep On Doing\" (1995)\n*\"Love The Way\" (1996)\n*\"I Gotta Get Away\" (1997)\n*\"What Was Said And Done\" (1997)\n\n===With Bomfunk MC's===\n\n===Albums===\n*1999 - ''[[In Stereo (Bomfunk MC's album)|In Stereo]]'' (Sony Music/Epidrome) (Worldwide)\n*2002 - ''[[Burnin' Sneakers]]'' (Sony Music/Epidrome) (Europe only [not UK])\n*2005 - ''[[Reverse Psychology]]'' (Universal Music/Polydor) (Europe only [not UK])\n\n===Singles===\n*\"Uprocking Beats (1998/1999) (UK, Germany, Sweden, Finland and Australia)\n*\"[[Freestyler (song)|Freestyler]]\" (1999 Finland only) (2000 Worldwide)\n*\"B-Boys & Flygirls\" (1999) (Finland, Denmark, Sweden, Germany, Australia)\n*\"Sky's The Limit\" (1999) (Promo only, Finland only) \n*\"Rocking Just To Make Ya Move\" (1999) (Finland only)\n*\"Other Emcees\" (1999) (Finland only) \n*\"Super Electric\" (2001) (UK and Europe - this was the band's last single in the UK)\n*\"Live Your Life\" (feat. Max'C) (2002) (\n*\"(Crack It!) [[I Know There's Something Going On|Something Goin' On\"]] (feat. [[Jessica Folcker]]).) (Finland Only, although it did appear internationally on the Fifa World Cup 2002 soundtrack album). \n*\"Back To Back\" (feat. Z-MC CD Single) 2002 (Finland only)\n*\"No Way In Hell\" (2004) (Europe excluding UK)\n*\"Hypnotic\" (feat. Elena Mady) (Scandinavia only) (2005)\n*\"Turn It Up\" (feat. [[Anna Nordell]] Radio Promo) (2005)\n\n===Solo===\n\n=== Appears On ===\n*Dynamite (CD, Single, Enh)  Epic  2004\n*Kool Kat Kollabo EP (2xLP)  Kool Kat Records  2003\n*This Is...Beats And Styles (CD, Album) Epic  2003\n*We're Not Ready Yet (CD, Album) Epic  2004\n*For My Peoples (CD) Kool Kat Records  2006\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Discogs artist|artist=B.O.+Dubb}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=1620564}}\n*[https://myspace.com/bfmcs Bomfunk MC's] on [[Myspace]]\n\n{{Bomfunk MC's}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ebanks, Raymond}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Finnish male musicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Helsinki]]\n[[Category:Finnish people of Jamaican descent]]\n[[Category:Finnish people of English descent]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Raymond Ebanks\n| birth name          = Raymond Anthony Ebanks\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1970|1|2|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[London]], [[England]]<ref>England and Wales Birth Registration Index, 1837-2008</ref>\n| image               =\n| caption             = Raymond Ebanks in 2012 (Ebanks, Darude, Max'C, Orkidea, Js16)\n| image_size          = \n| background          = solo_singer\n| alias               = B.O. Dubb, B.O.W.\n| origin              = \n| genre               = [[Electronica]], [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n| years_active        = 1994-2006; 2011\n| label               = \n| associated_acts     = [[Bomfunk MC's]], Soup De loop, [[Beats And Styles]], Kollabo Brothers\n| website             = \n}}\n\n'''Raymond Anthony Ebanks''', aka '''B.O. Dubb''' (formerly known as B.O.W.; born 2 January 1970) is a semi-retired [[Finland|Finnish]] [[rap music|rapper]] best known as the frontman of the hip-hop group the [[Bomfunk MC's]].\n\n== Early career ==\n\nRaymond was born in [[London]] to a [[Jamaica]]n-[[England|English]] father and a Finnish mother. He began recording music as a teenager in the early 90s as part of the hip hop group \"The Master Brothers\", who often performed over DJ sets at clubs. Whilst no recordings were made, some of their performances were recorded, and have emerged online. Around this time, Raymond performed guest raps on the song Cryin' Out by Rama (1994).\n\n== Soup De Loop ==\n\nIn 1995, Raymond teamed up with longtime producer Jaakko \"[[JS16]]\" Salovaara and singer Mari Vesala to form the pop group Soup De Loop, and signed to the now defunct Blue Bubble Records. Their music was a combination of female sung house and G-Funk hip hop music, with Mari singing and Raymond providing raps. The group released an album, \"Brainspotting\" in 1997, as well as several singles including \"Keep On Doing\", which was a hit in Finland and appeared on several dance compilations around the time. Despite this, the group didn't have any success outside Finland. Mari left the group some time after the album was released, and they broke up rather than look for another singer.\n\n== Bomfunk MCs - 1999-2005 ==\n\nAfter the breakup of Soup De Loop, Ebanks and Salovaara teamed up with DJ Ismo \"DJ Gismo\" Lappalainen to form Bomfunk MCs. The band were signed to Sony Music Finland due to Blue Bubble Records going down under. The band quickly became known for the breakdancing in their videos and the graffiti in their album cover designs, both things which contributed to their popularity. Despite the associations with breakdancing, the band did perform slower paced hip hop songs as well and some more trancey material later on. The group released two albums with DJ Gismo - [[In Stereo (Bomfunk MC's album)|In Stereo]] and [[Burnin' Sneakers]], and released a number of successful singles, the most notable of which being [[Uprocking Beats]] and [[Freestyler (song)|Freestyler]]. Freestyler in particular became the band's signature song, which they are still remembered for to this day.\n\nThe band remained popular in Finland and Europe, but lost popularity elsewhere and their last release in the UK was \"Super Electric\", whose parent album, [[Burnin' Sneakers]] was never released in the UK due to poor sales of the single. However, the band contributed the official World Cup 2002 song for Sweden \"[[I Know There's Something Going On|(Crack It) Something Goin' On]]\", as well as contributed \"Put Your Hands Up\" and \"We R Atomic\" to the PlayStation game [[Firebugs (video game)|Firebugs]], in which they appeared as playable characters. These appearances revived the band's popularity in the UK, but it wasn't enough for the album to be released there. DJ Gismo left Bomfunk MCs in 2002 in order to join the group Stonedeep. He was replaced by Skillsters duo, which consists of Riku Pentti (DJ) and Okke Komulainen (keyboards).\n\nIn 2004, Salovaara guested on a number of songs by [[Beats And Styles]]. These have been erroneously credited as Bomfunk MC's songs, although the only real difference is the producer.\n\nIn 2005, the group signed to Universal/Polydor and recorded the album \"Reverse Psychology\". This album was very different to the previous two, as it had far more of a straightforward hip hop sound, in that respect, more in common with the \"Soup De Loop\" material. The album was half produced by Salovaara, and the other half by Pentti and Komulainen. The band also experimented more with trance inspired songs such as \"Hypnotic\" and \"Turn It Up\", and dance-rock songs such as \"No Way In Hell\" and \"Reverse Psychology\". The album also featured a guest appearance from [[Kurtis Blow]], of [[The Breaks (Kurtis Blow song)|The Breaks]] fame. Whilst the album produced the big European hit \"No Way In Hell\", it quickly became rare and obscure, due to only being released in Scandinavia, Germany and Eastern Europe. DJ Gismo appears on the cover of the album despite not contributing to it, this is likely to be for marketing reasons.\n\nA while after the release of the album, the group quietly split up. It has said this was due to Ebanks desire to retire from the spotlight. Salovaara has continued producing music.\n\n== Post-Bomfunk MCs ==\n\nSince Bomfunk MC's breakup, Ebanks has largely disappeared from the music industry, although he did guest on a few tracks.\n\nIn 2011 a Finnish rap compilation \"{{lang|fi|Rappiotaidetta: Suomir\u00e4pin Vaippaik\u00e4}}\" was released, which features Ebanks performing a song entitled \"{{lang|fi|Keijo Ei Pelaa}}\" under the pseudonym Keijo K from 1990. It is possibly the only released recording of Ebanks rapping in Finnish.\n\nIn 2014 Soup De Loop's album Brainspotting appeared for digital download worldwide, after being an out of print and expensive Finland-only release for years. The masters were owned by Sony-BMG who had taken over the Blue Bubble Label on which the album was originally released.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===with Soup De Loop===\n\n===Albums===\n\"Brainspotting\" (1997)\n\n===Singles===\n*\"Keep On Doing\" (1995)\n*\"Love The Way\" (1996)\n*\"I Gotta Get Away\" (1997)\n*\"What Was Said And Done\" (1997)\n\n===with Bomfunk MC's===\n\n===Albums===\n*1999 - ''[[In Stereo (Bomfunk MC's album)|In Stereo]]'' (Sony Music/Epidrome) (Worldwide)\n*2002 - ''[[Burnin' Sneakers]]'' (Sony Music/Epidrome) (Europe only [not UK])\n*2005 - ''[[Reverse Psychology]]'' (Universal Music/Polydor) (Europe only [not UK])\n\n===Singles===\n*\"Uprocking Beats (1998/1999) (UK, Germany, Sweden, Finland and Australia)\n*\"[[Freestyler (song)|Freestyler]]\" (1999 Finland only) (2000 Worldwide)\n*\"B-Boys & Flygirls\" (1999) (Finland, Denmark, Sweden, Germany, Australia)\n*\"Sky's The Limit\" (1999) (Promo only, Finland only) \n*\"Rocking Just To Make Ya Move\" (1999) (Finland only)\n*\"Other Emcees\" (1999) (Finland only) \n*\"Super Electric\" (2001) (UK and Europe - this was the band's last single in the UK)\n*\"Live Your Life\" (feat. Max'C) (2002) (\n*\"(Crack It!) [[I Know There's Something Going On|Something Goin' On\"]] (feat. [[Jessica Folcker]]).) (Finland Only, although it did appear internationally on the Fifa World Cup 2002 soundtrack album). \n*\"Back To Back\" (feat. Z-MC CD Single) 2002 (Finland only)\n*\"No Way In Hell\" (2004) (Europe excluding UK)\n*\"Hypnotic\" (feat. Elena Mady) (Scandinavia only) (2005)\n*\"Turn It Up\" (feat. [[Anna Nordell]] Radio Promo) (2005)\n\n===Solo===\n\n=== Appears On ===\n*Dynamite (CD, Single, Enh)  Epic  2004\n*Kool Kat Kollabo EP (2xLP)  Kool Kat Records  2003\n*This Is...Beats And Styles (CD, Album) Epic  2003\n*We're Not Ready Yet (CD, Album) Epic  2004\n*For My Peoples (CD) Kool Kat Records  2006\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Discogs artist|artist=B.O.+Dubb}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=1620564}}\n*[https://myspace.com/bfmcs Bomfunk MC's] on [[Myspace]]\n\n{{Bomfunk MC's}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ebanks, Raymond}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Finnish male musicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Helsinki]]\n[[Category:Finnish people of Jamaican descent]]\n[[Category:Finnish people of English descent]]\n", "name_user": "Hisham Boutimah", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ewith Soup De Loop", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raymond_Ebanks"}
{"title_page": "Rudratej Singh", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian business executive}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Rudratej Singh\n| image              = Rudratej Singh during an auto event.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = 1973 or 1974\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = {{death date and given age|2020|4|20|46|df=y}}\n| death_place        = \n| resting_place      = \n| nationality        = Indian\n| other_names        = \n| known_for          = Career in [[Royal Enfield (India)|Royal Enfield Motors]] and [[Unilever]]\n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[Air Force Bal Bharati School]]<br>[[Delhi University]]<br>[[IMT Ghaziabad]]\n| employer           = [[BMW India]]\n| occupation         = [[CEO]], [[President (corporate title)|President]]\n| years_active       = \n| home_town          = \n| networth           = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| partner            = \n| children           = \n}}\n\n'''Rudratej Singh''' (1973 or 1974 \u2013 20 April 2020) was an Indian business executive. He was the President and CEO of [[BMW India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/sectors/auto/former-royal-enfield-chief-rudratej-singh-to-now-lead-bmw-india/story/357547.html|title=Former Royal Enfield chief Rudratej Singh to now lead BMW India|website=www.businesstoday.in|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/auto-news/rudratej-singh-former-royal-enfield-president-to-head-bmw-india-1560945636948.html|title=Rudratej Singh, former Royal Enfield boss, to head BMW India|last=Panday|first=Amit|date=19 June 2019|website=Livemint.com|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> Singh was also Global President of [[Royal Enfield (India)|Royal Enfield Motors Limited]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://auto.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/bmw-appoints-ex-royal-enfield-chief-rudratej-singh-appointed-as-president-ceo-of-india-operations/69859474|title=Ex-Royal Enfield sales head Rudratej Singh appointed as President & CEO of BMW Group India - ET Auto|website=[[The Economic Times]]|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> and Vice President of [[Unilever]] in Singapore.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\n==Early life and education==\nSingh grew up in New Delhi. He completed his schooling from [[Air Force Bal Bharati School]], batch of 1990. He graduated in Commerce from [[Delhi University]] in 1993 and then moved on to the [[IMT Ghaziabad]] to study MBA in Marketing and Finance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inshorts.com/en/news/rudratej-singh-former-royal-enfield-president-to-head-bmw-india-1561001423685|title=Rudratej Singh, former Royal Enfield President, to head BMW India|website=Inshorts - Stay Informed|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> In 2014, he undertook Advanced Management Program from [[Harvard Business School]].\n\n==Career==\nSingh started his career in 1996 as a Senior Product Manager at the [[Dabur|Dabur India Limited]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.autoactu.com/rudratej-singh-nomme-president-directeur-general-de-bmw-group-inde.shtml|title=autoactu.com - l'information automobile professionnelle|website=www.autoactu.com|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> He then joined as Area Sales Manager in [[Hindustan Unilever]] in August 1998. In 2000, he was then promoted to Sr Brand Manager, within Hindustan Unilever,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/magazine/event/business-today-honda-pro-am-of-champions-event/story/12884.html|title=Happy Valley- Business News|website=www.businesstoday.in|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> where he was one of the key people to create the Brooke Bond master brand. He then held senior positions in the Hindustan Unilever Ltd and Unilever PLC across various developed and developing markets globally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/company-officers/EICH.NSf|title=${Instrument_CompanyName} ${Instrument_Ric} People {{!}} Reuters.com|last=Editorial|first=Reuters|website=U.S.|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/rudratej-singh-appointed-bmw-group-india-president-and-chief-executive-119061901266_1.html|title=Rudratej Singh appointed BMW Group India President and Chief Executive|last=Narasimhan|first=T. E.|date=19 June 2019|work=Business Standard India|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2015, he moved from Unilever and joined Eicher Motors Limited (EML) as their President of flagship motorcycle business, Royal Enfield and member of the Management Team of [[Eicher Motors|Eicher Motors Limited]] (EML).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://overdrive.in/news-cars-auto/rudratej-singh-quits-royal-enfield-with-immediate-effect/|title=Rudratej Singh quits Royal Enfield with immediate effect|website=Overdrive|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref>  In 2017, Singh was promoted to the Global President of Royal Enfield.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/bmw-group-names-rudratej-singh-as-president-and-ceo-for-india-4116681.html|title=BMW Group names Rudratej Singh as president and CEO for India|website=Moneycontrol|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/royal-enfield-appoints-rudratej-singh-as-president/articleshow/45929893.cms|title=Royal Enfield appoints Rudratej Singh as President|date=19 January 2015|work=The Economic Times|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/auto/auto-news/story/royal-enfield-sets-up-direct-sales-subsidiary-in-the-us-plans-to-open-retail-stores-288812-2015-08-18|title=Royal Enfield sets up direct sales subsidiary in the US; plans to open retail stores|last=DelhiAugust 18|first=Press Trust of India New|last2=August 18|first2=2015UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019|last3=Ist|first3=2015 10:19}}</ref> During his four year tenure, he helped Royal Enfield become one of the most profitable auto companies in the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/royal-enfields-rudratej-singh-quits/article25941078.ece|title=Rudratej Singh quits Royal Enfield|last=PTI|website=@businessline|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/super-50-companies-2015/eicher-motors-its-all-in-the-drive/40705/1|title=Eicher Motors: It's all in the drive|website=Forbes India|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> His efforts also helped grow the company\u2019s market share in India from 3.3%, in 2014, to 6.9%, in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eicher.in/uploads/1518004619_press-release-eicher-motors-results-Q3-2017-18.pdf|title=Eicher Motors Limited registers record performance in the quarter ended December 31st, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloombergquint.com/markets/eicher-motors-stock-jumps-on-plan-to-increase-royal-enfield-capacity|title=Eicher Motors' Stock Jumps On Plan To Increase Royal Enfield Capacity|website=BloombergQuint|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Singh quit Royal Enfield after serving for four years<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/two-wheelers/royal-enfield-president-rudratej-singh-quits-lalit-malik-to-take-charge/articleshow/67438710.cms|title=Royal Enfield President Rudratej Singh quits, Lalit Malik to take charge|date=8 January 2019|work=The Economic Times|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autocarpro.in/News/royal-enfield\u2019s-president-rudratej-singh-quits-41770|title=Royal Enfield's president Rudratej Singh quits|website=Autocarpro.in|language=en-US|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> and joined BMW India as its President and Chief Executive Officer (CEO) with his term starting from August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zeebiz.com/automobile/news-bmw-group-india-gets-new-ceo-who-is-rudratej-rudy-singh-profile-102807|title=BMW Group India gets new CEO - Who is Rudratej 'Rudy' Singh? Profile|date=19 June 2019|website=Zee Business|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afaqs.com/people-spotting/463_Former-Enfield-hand-Rudratej-Singh-joins-BMW-India-as-president-and-CEO|title=Former Enfield hand Rudratej Singh joins BMW India as president and CEO|date=23 June 2019|website=www.afaqs.com|language=en-US|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://auto.ndtv.com/news/rudratej-singh-appointed-president-and-ceo-of-bmw-group-india-2055903|title=Rudratej Singh Appointed President And CEO Of BMW Group India - NDTV CarAndBike|website=CarAndBike|language=English|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> He died on 20 April 2020 at the age of 46 from cardiac arrest.<ref>[http://everythingexperiential.businessworld.in/article/Rudratej-Singh-President-CEO-of-BMW-Group-India-is-no-more/20-04-2020-189621/ Rudratej Singh, President & CEO of BMW Group India is no more]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/bmw-india-ceo-rudratej-singh-passes-away-due-to-cardiac-arrest/articleshow/75251335.cms|title=Rudratej Singh: BMW India CEO Rudratej Singh passes away due to cardiac arrest {{!}} India Business News - Times of India|last=20 Apr|first=PTI {{!}} Updated:|last2=2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=23 April 2020|last3=Ist|first3=23:33}}</ref>\n\n== Other activities ==\nSingh represented India as an amateur golfer and won 18 titles globally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://overdrive.in/news-cars-auto/rudratej-singh-appointed-as-new-president-of-royal-enfield/|title=Rudratej Singh appointed as new president of Royal Enfield|website=Overdrive|language=en|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref> He was also a board member of the Women\u2019s Golf Association of India (WGAI),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://issuu.com/golfdigestindia/docs/gd_02_2018/34|title=Golf Digest India - February 2018|website=Issuu|language=en|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref> and helped run a charity for underprivileged (girl) children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cmocouncil.org/profiles/7486|title=Members - CMO Council\u2122|website=www.cmocouncil.org|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref> He spoke regularly at various business and brand forums across the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autocarindia.com/bike-news/rudratej-singh-is-royal-enfield8217s-new-president-392882|title=Rudratej Singh is Royal Enfield's new President|website=Autocar India|language=en|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and honors==\n* 2012 - Marketer of the Year by the World CMO Council - Asia<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiainfoline.com/article/news-top-story/royal-enfield-appoints-rudratej-singh-as-president-115011900010_1.html|title=Royal Enfield appoints Rudratej Singh as President|website=www.indiainfoline.com|language=en|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref>\n*2007 - Hindustan Unilever Directors Award<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/hul-allcargo-top-honchos-win-the-last-leg-of-et-golf/articleshow/5635162.cms?from=mdr|title=HUL, Allcargo top honchos win the last leg of ET golf|date=3 March 2010|work=The Economic Times|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Rudratej}}\n[[Category:1970s births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:BMW people]]\n[[Category:Institute of Management Technology, Ghaziabad alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Delhi alumni]]\n[[Category:Place of death missing]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Harvard Business School Advanced Management Program attendees]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian business executive}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Rudratej Singh\n| image              = Rudratej Singh during an auto event.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = 1973 or 1974\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = {{death date and given age|2020|4|20|46|df=y}}\n| death_place        = \n| resting_place      = \n| nationality        = Indian\n| other_names        = \n| known_for          = Career in [[Royal Enfield (India)|Royal Enfield Motors]] and [[Unilever]]\n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[Air Force Bal Bharati School]]<br>[[Delhi University]]<br>[[IMT Ghaziabad]]\n| employer           = [[BMW India]]\n| occupation         = [[CEO]], [[President (corporate title)|President]]\n| years_active       = \n| home_town          = \n| networth           = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| partner            = \n| children           = \n}}\n\n'''Rudratej Singh''' (1973 or 1974 \u2013 20 April 2020) was an Indian business executive. He was the President and CEO of [[BMW India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/sectors/auto/former-royal-enfield-chief-rudratej-singh-to-now-lead-bmw-india/story/357547.html|title=Former Royal Enfield chief Rudratej Singh to now lead BMW India|website=www.businesstoday.in|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/auto-news/rudratej-singh-former-royal-enfield-president-to-head-bmw-india-1560945636948.html|title=Rudratej Singh, former Royal Enfield boss, to head BMW India|last=Panday|first=Amit|date=19 June 2019|website=Livemint.com|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> Singh was also Global President of [[Royal Enfield (India)|Royal Enfield Motors Limited]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://auto.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/bmw-appoints-ex-royal-enfield-chief-rudratej-singh-appointed-as-president-ceo-of-india-operations/69859474|title=Ex-Royal Enfield sales head Rudratej Singh appointed as President & CEO of BMW Group India - ET Auto|website=[[The Economic Times]]|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> and Vice President of [[Unilever]] in Singapore.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\n==Early life and education==\nSingh grew up in New Delhi. He completed his schooling from [[Air Force Bal Bharati School]], batch of 1990. He graduated in Commerce from [[Delhi University]] in 1993 and then moved on to the [[IMT Ghaziabad]] to study MBA in Marketing and Finance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inshorts.com/en/news/rudratej-singh-former-royal-enfield-president-to-head-bmw-india-1561001423685|title=Rudratej Singh, former Royal Enfield President, to head BMW India|website=Inshorts - Stay Informed|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> In 2014, he undertook Advanced Management Program from [[Harvard Business School]].\n\n==Career==\nSingh started his career in 1996 as a Senior Product Manager at the [[Dabur|Dabur India Limited]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.autoactu.com/rudratej-singh-nomme-president-directeur-general-de-bmw-group-inde.shtml|title=autoactu.com - l'information automobile professionnelle|website=www.autoactu.com|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> He then joined as Area Sales Manager in [[Hindustan Unilever]] in August 1998. In 2000, he was then promoted to Sr Brand Manager, within Hindustan Unilever,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/magazine/event/business-today-honda-pro-am-of-champions-event/story/12884.html|title=Happy Valley- Business News|website=www.businesstoday.in|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> where he was one of the key people to create the Brooke Bond master brand. He then held senior positions in the Hindustan Unilever Ltd and Unilever PLC across various developed and developing markets globally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/company-officers/EICH.NSf|title=${Instrument_CompanyName} ${Instrument_Ric} People {{!}} Reuters.com|last=Editorial|first=Reuters|website=U.S.|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/rudratej-singh-appointed-bmw-group-india-president-and-chief-executive-119061901266_1.html|title=Rudratej Singh appointed BMW Group India President and Chief Executive|last=Narasimhan|first=T. E.|date=19 June 2019|work=Business Standard India|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn Jan 2015, he moved from Unilever and joined Eicher Motors Limited (EML) as their President of flagship motorcycle business, Royal Enfield and member of the Management Team of [[Eicher Motors|Eicher Motors Limited]] (EML).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://overdrive.in/news-cars-auto/rudratej-singh-quits-royal-enfield-with-immediate-effect/|title=Rudratej Singh quits Royal Enfield with immediate effect|website=Overdrive|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref>  In 2017, Singh was promoted to the Global President of Royal Enfield.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/bmw-group-names-rudratej-singh-as-president-and-ceo-for-india-4116681.html|title=BMW Group names Rudratej Singh as president and CEO for India|website=Moneycontrol|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/royal-enfield-appoints-rudratej-singh-as-president/articleshow/45929893.cms|title=Royal Enfield appoints Rudratej Singh as President|date=19 January 2015|work=The Economic Times|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/auto/auto-news/story/royal-enfield-sets-up-direct-sales-subsidiary-in-the-us-plans-to-open-retail-stores-288812-2015-08-18|title=Royal Enfield sets up direct sales subsidiary in the US; plans to open retail stores|last=DelhiAugust 18|first=Press Trust of India New|last2=August 18|first2=2015UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019|last3=Ist|first3=2015 10:19}}</ref> During his four year tenure, he helped Royal Enfield become one of the most profitable auto companies in the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/royal-enfields-rudratej-singh-quits/article25941078.ece|title=Rudratej Singh quits Royal Enfield|last=PTI|website=@businessline|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/super-50-companies-2015/eicher-motors-its-all-in-the-drive/40705/1|title=Eicher Motors: It's all in the drive|website=Forbes India|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> His efforts also helped grow the company\u2019s market share in India from 3.3%, in 2014, to 6.9%, in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eicher.in/uploads/1518004619_press-release-eicher-motors-results-Q3-2017-18.pdf|title=Eicher Motors Limited registers record performance in the quarter ended December 31st, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloombergquint.com/markets/eicher-motors-stock-jumps-on-plan-to-increase-royal-enfield-capacity|title=Eicher Motors' Stock Jumps On Plan To Increase Royal Enfield Capacity|website=BloombergQuint|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Singh quit Royal Enfield after serving for four years<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/two-wheelers/royal-enfield-president-rudratej-singh-quits-lalit-malik-to-take-charge/articleshow/67438710.cms|title=Royal Enfield President Rudratej Singh quits, Lalit Malik to take charge|date=8 January 2019|work=The Economic Times|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autocarpro.in/News/royal-enfield\u2019s-president-rudratej-singh-quits-41770|title=Royal Enfield's president Rudratej Singh quits|website=Autocarpro.in|language=en-US|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> and joined BMW India as its President and Chief Executive Officer (CEO) with his term starting from August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zeebiz.com/automobile/news-bmw-group-india-gets-new-ceo-who-is-rudratej-rudy-singh-profile-102807|title=BMW Group India gets new CEO - Who is Rudratej 'Rudy' Singh? Profile|date=19 June 2019|website=Zee Business|language=en|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afaqs.com/people-spotting/463_Former-Enfield-hand-Rudratej-Singh-joins-BMW-India-as-president-and-CEO|title=Former Enfield hand Rudratej Singh joins BMW India as president and CEO|date=23 June 2019|website=www.afaqs.com|language=en-US|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://auto.ndtv.com/news/rudratej-singh-appointed-president-and-ceo-of-bmw-group-india-2055903|title=Rudratej Singh Appointed President And CEO Of BMW Group India - NDTV CarAndBike|website=CarAndBike|language=English|access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> He died on 20 April 2020 at the age of 46 from cardiac arrest.<ref>[http://everythingexperiential.businessworld.in/article/Rudratej-Singh-President-CEO-of-BMW-Group-India-is-no-more/20-04-2020-189621/ Rudratej Singh, President & CEO of BMW Group India is no more]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/bmw-india-ceo-rudratej-singh-passes-away-due-to-cardiac-arrest/articleshow/75251335.cms|title=Rudratej Singh: BMW India CEO Rudratej Singh passes away due to cardiac arrest {{!}} India Business News - Times of India|last=20 Apr|first=PTI {{!}} Updated:|last2=2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=23 April 2020|last3=Ist|first3=23:33}}</ref>\n\n== Other activities ==\nSingh represented India as an amateur golfer and won 18 titles globally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://overdrive.in/news-cars-auto/rudratej-singh-appointed-as-new-president-of-royal-enfield/|title=Rudratej Singh appointed as new president of Royal Enfield|website=Overdrive|language=en|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref> He was also a board member of the Women\u2019s Golf Association of India (WGAI),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://issuu.com/golfdigestindia/docs/gd_02_2018/34|title=Golf Digest India - February 2018|website=Issuu|language=en|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref> and helped run a charity for underprivileged (girl) children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cmocouncil.org/profiles/7486|title=Members - CMO Council\u2122|website=www.cmocouncil.org|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref> He spoke regularly at various business and brand forums across the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autocarindia.com/bike-news/rudratej-singh-is-royal-enfield8217s-new-president-392882|title=Rudratej Singh is Royal Enfield's new President|website=Autocar India|language=en|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and honors==\n* 2012 - Marketer of the Year by the World CMO Council - Asia<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiainfoline.com/article/news-top-story/royal-enfield-appoints-rudratej-singh-as-president-115011900010_1.html|title=Royal Enfield appoints Rudratej Singh as President|website=www.indiainfoline.com|language=en|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref>\n*2007 - Hindustan Unilever Directors Award<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/hul-allcargo-top-honchos-win-the-last-leg-of-et-golf/articleshow/5635162.cms?from=mdr|title=HUL, Allcargo top honchos win the last leg of ET golf|date=3 March 2010|work=The Economic Times|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Rudratej}}\n[[Category:1970s births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:BMW people]]\n[[Category:Institute of Management Technology, Ghaziabad alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Delhi alumni]]\n[[Category:Place of death missing]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Harvard Business School Advanced Management Program attendees]]\n", "name_user": "Ionmars10", "label": "safe", "comment": "expand month names", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rudratej_Singh"}
{"title_page": "Goursez Vreizh", "text_new": "{{Infobox Organization\n|name         =  <small>Fraternity of the Druids, Bards and Ovates of Brittany</small><br><small>''Breudeuriezh Drouized, Barzhed hag Ovizion Breizh''</small>\n|image        = Tribann.svg\n|caption      = ''[[Awen]] of Iolo Morganwg.''\n|size         = 120px\n|abbreviation = Goursez Vreizh\n|formation    = 1899\n|headquarters = [[Brittany]]\n|type         = [[Breton culture]]<BR>[[Celtic Revival]]\n|founder      = [[Jean Le Fustec]]\n|leader      =  \n|website      = [http://www.gorsedd.com/ gorsedd.com]\n}}\n\n'''Goursez Vreizh''' (officially '''Breudeuriezh Drouized, Barzhed hag Ovizion Breizh''') is the national [[gorsedd]] of [[Brittany]] (\"Breizh\" in [[Breton language|Breton]]). It often has delegates from the [[Welsh language|Welsh]] [[gorsedd]] and [[Gorsedh Kernow]] in [[Cornwall]]. The Breton organisation is itself based on the Welsh-based [[Gorsedd]], which was founded by [[Iolo Morganwg]] in 1792.\n\n==History==\n\n[[Th\u00e9odore Hersart de la Villemarqu\u00e9]] (1815-1895) was the first Breton to be made an initiate by the Gorsedd of Wales. He took the bardic name Hersart Kervarker. He created a \"Fraternity of the Bards of Brittany\" (Breuriez Breiz) but this did not lead to the creation of a Gorsedd.\n\n* 1838: La Villemarqu\u00e9, [[Auguste Brizeux]] and [[Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Le Gonidec]] are adopted as honorary members of the ''Cymdeithas Cymreigyddion y Fenny'' (Abergavenny Celtic Union).\n* 1843 (or possibly 1857, evidence is unclear): La Villemarqu\u00e9 founds the ''Breuriez-Breiz'' (Breton Brotherhood), whose activity is restricted to arts and linguistics, is founded.\n* 1867: A small Welsh delegation goes to the international [[Celtic Congress]].\n* August 16, 1898: The [[Breton Regionalist Union]] is founded.\n* 1899: A Breton delegation of twenty people is received at the Gorsedd of Wales in order to constitute the core of a Breton group. The Breton guests are made [[ovates]], but not fully initiated. This year is regarded as the founding year of the Goursez.\n* September 1, 1900: The new constitutive assembly meets in an inn at [[Guingamp]]. Jean Le Fustec (with the bardic name Yann ab Gwilherm; later Lemenik) becomes the first Grand Druid of the \"Gorsedd of Lesser Britain\".\n* November 23, 1908: The ''Gorsedd Barzed Gourenez Breiz Izel'' (Gorsedd of the Bards of the Peninsula of Brittany) is officially proclaimed. \n* 1936: A split in the Goursez causes the formation of the explicitly neo-pagan [[Kredenn Geltiek Hollvedel]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.angelfire.com/folk/boutios/histoirekg.html|title=..:: LES DRUIDES DU QU\u00e9BEC /{{!}}\\ ::..|website=www.angelfire.com|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n==Grand Druids==\n\n* [[Jean Le Fustec]] from 1900 to 1903.\n* [[Erwan Berthou]] (also known as Kaledvoulc'h) from 1904 to 1932.\n* [[Fran\u00e7ois Taldir-Jaffrennou]] from 1933 to 1955.\n* [[P\u00ear Loisel]]-Eostig Sarzhaw from 1956 to 1980.\n* [[Gwenc'hlan Le Scou\u00ebzec]] from 1981 to 2008.\n* [[Per Vari Kerloc'h]] from 2008.\n\n==Gallery==\n\n<gallery>\nImage:PhotoGorsedd.jpg|Assembly of druids of the Gorsedd, 1906\nImage:Bardes Gouarec.jpg|Bards of the Gorsedd singing ''Bro goz ma Zadou'', 1907\nImage:GorseddDigorHanvec1.jpg|Centenary celebration of the Gorsedd, 1999\nImage:Le Scouezec.jpg|Grand Druid [[Gwenc'hlan Le Scou\u00ebzec]], 2007\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060826182529/http://www.gorsethkernow.org.uk/english/news/breton02.htm Breton Gorseth 2002]\n\n[[Category:Breton language]]\n[[Category:Breton mythology and folklore]]\n[[Category:Gorseddau|Breizh]]\n[[Category:Inter-Celtic organisations]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Organization\n|name         =  <small>Fraternity of the Druids, Bards and Ovates of Brittany</small><br><small>''Breudeuriezh Drouized, Barzhed hag Ovizion Breizh''</small>\n|image        = Tribann.svg\n|caption      = ''[[Awen]] of Iolo Morganwg.''\n|size         = 120px\n|abbreviation = Goursez Vreizh\n|formation    = 1900\n|headquarters = [[Brittany]]\n|type         = [[Breton culture]]<BR>[[Celtic Revival]]\n|founder      = [[Jean Le Fustec]]\n|leader      =  \n|website      = [http://www.gorsedd.com/ gorsedd.com]\n}}\n\n'''Goursez Vreizh''' (officially '''Breudeuriezh Drouized, Barzhed hag Ovizion Breizh''') is the national [[gorsedd]] of [[Brittany]] (\"Breizh\" in [[Breton language|Breton]]). It often has delegates from the [[Welsh language|Welsh]] [[gorsedd]] and [[Gorsedh Kernow]] in [[Cornwall]]. The Breton organisation is itself based on the Welsh-based [[Gorsedd]], which was founded by [[Iolo Morganwg]] in 1792.\n\n==History==\n\n[[Th\u00e9odore Hersart de la Villemarqu\u00e9]] (1815-1895) was the first Breton to be made an initiate by the Gorsedd of Wales. He took the bardic name Hersart Kervarker. He created a \"Fraternity of the Bards of Brittany\" (Breuriez Breiz) but this did not lead to the creation of a Gorsedd.\n\n* 1838: La Villemarqu\u00e9, [[Auguste Brizeux]] and [[Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Le Gonidec]] are adopted as honorary members of the ''Cymdeithas Cymreigyddion y Fenny'' (Abergavenny Celtic Union).\n* 1843 (or possibly 1857, evidence is unclear): La Villemarqu\u00e9 founds the ''Breuriez-Breiz'' (Breton Brotherhood), whose activity is restricted to arts and linguistics, is founded.\n* 1867: A small Welsh delegation goes to the international [[Celtic Congress]].\n* August 16, 1898: The [[Breton Regionalist Union]] is founded.\n* 1899: A Breton delegation of twenty people is received at the Gorsedd of Wales in order to constitute the core of a Breton group. The Breton guests are made [[ovates]], but not fully initiated. This year is regarded as the founding year of the Goursez.\n* September 1, 1900: The new constitutive assembly meets in an inn at [[Guingamp]]. Jean Le Fustec (with the bardic name Yann ab Gwilherm; later Lemenik) becomes the first Grand Druid of the \"Gorsedd of Lesser Britain\".\n* November 23, 1908: The ''Gorsedd Barzed Gourenez Breiz Izel'' (Gorsedd of the Bards of the Peninsula of Brittany) is officially proclaimed. \n* 1936: A split in the Goursez causes the formation of the explicitly neo-pagan [[Kredenn Geltiek Hollvedel]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.angelfire.com/folk/boutios/histoirekg.html|title=..:: LES DRUIDES DU QU\u00e9BEC /{{!}}\\ ::..|website=www.angelfire.com|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n==Grand Druids==\n\n* [[Jean Le Fustec]] from 1900 to 1903.\n* [[Erwan Berthou]] (also known as Kaledvoulc'h) from 1904 to 1932.\n* [[Fran\u00e7ois Taldir-Jaffrennou]] from 1933 to 1955.\n* [[P\u00ear Loisel]]-Eostig Sarzhaw from 1956 to 1980.\n* [[Gwenc'hlan Le Scou\u00ebzec]] from 1981 to 2008.\n* [[Per Vari Kerloc'h]] from 2008.\n\n==Gallery==\n\n<gallery>\nImage:PhotoGorsedd.jpg|Assembly of druids of the Gorsedd, 1906\nImage:Bardes Gouarec.jpg|Bards of the Gorsedd singing ''Bro goz ma Zadou'', 1907\nImage:GorseddDigorHanvec1.jpg|Centenary celebration of the Gorsedd, 1999\nImage:Le Scouezec.jpg|Grand Druid [[Gwenc'hlan Le Scou\u00ebzec]], 2007\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060826182529/http://www.gorsethkernow.org.uk/english/news/breton02.htm Breton Gorseth 2002]\n\n[[Category:Breton language]]\n[[Category:Breton mythology and folklore]]\n[[Category:Gorseddau|Breizh]]\n[[Category:Inter-Celtic organisations]]\n", "name_user": "ProletariatetsBefrielseOrkester", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goursez_Vreizh"}
{"title_page": "Toosie Slide", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 song by Drake}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Toosie Slide\n| cover      = Drake - Toosie Slide.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2020|4|3|mf=y}}\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres --> [[trap music|Trap]]<ref name=\"COS\" />\n| length     = {{duration|m=4|s=7}}\n| label      =\n* [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n* [[OVO Sound|OVO]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Drake (musician)|Aubrey Graham]]\n* Nick Kobe\n* [[OZ (record producer)|Ozan Yildirim]]\n| producer   = [[OZ (record producer)|OZ]]\n| prev_title = [[Oprah's Bank Account]]\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|xWggTb45brM|\"Toosie Slide\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Toosie Slide'''\" is a song by Canadian rapper [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]. It was released on April 3, 2020, through [[Republic Records|Republic]] and [[OVO Sound|OVO]].<ref name=\"forbes\"/> The song is titled after social media influencer Toosie who had previously helped the song go viral.<ref name=\"Rap Up\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2020/04/02/new-music-drake-toosie-slide/|title=Drake Returns With New Single \"Toosie Slide\"|work=[[Rap-Up]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> A video was released alongside the song, showing Drake [[quarantined]], due to the ongoing [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]]. He is seen on the video wearing a mask and a pair of gloves to signify the safety precautions that have been taken globally to curb the spread of the virus. He also demonstrates the Toosie Slide dance in his [[Toronto]] mansion. The song debuted at number one on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart, making Drake the first male artist to accomplish three number-one debuts.<ref name=\"TS BB\"/>\n\n==Background and promotion==\nOn March 29, 2020, social media influencer Toosie uploaded a clip showing him and his friends doing a dance challenge called the \"Toosie Slide\" while parts of the song are playing in the background.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/03/drake-unreleased-toosie-slide-snippet-tiktok|title=Drake Could Be Primed for TikTok Domination After Snippet From Unreleased Song Inspires \"Toosie Slide\" (UPDATE)|last=Martinez|first=Jose|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/unclick/drake-toosie-slide-tiktok/|title=Reportedly unreleased Drake track leads to viral TikTok dance|last=Schroeder|first=Audra|work=[[Daily Dot]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> The dance was described as a \"modern day '[[Cha Cha Slide]]' by [[DJ Casper]]\" and went viral after it was introduced to the app [[TikTok]] by Toosie, Hiii Key and Michigan duo [[Ayo & Teo]].<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/laurenalvarez/2020/03/31/drake-announces-new-single-toosie-slide-coming-thursday-night/#761fe0c279fd|title=Drake Announces New Single \"Toosie Slide\" Coming Thursday Night|last=Alvarez|first=Lauren|work=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"rollingstone\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/drake-toosie-slide-song-977734/|title=Drake Grooves Down Empty Street and Mansion in Video for \"Toosie Slide\"|last=Legaspi|first=Althea|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> When it was subsequently shared on other social media pages, people considered possible involvement by Drake.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hiphop-n-more.com/2020/03/new-drake-song-tik-tok-toosie-slide/|title=Drake Previews New Tik Tok-Type Song for \"Toosie Slide\": Listen|author=Navjosh|website=HipHopNMore|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> He hinted at an impending release, saying \"I'mma drop soon since ya'll got it going insane\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/drake-promises-to-drop-newly-teased-song-news.107507.html|title=Drake Promises To Drop Newly Teased Song|last=A.|first=Aron|website=[[HotNewHipHop]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> Drake then took to his social media on March 31, 2020, to declare the song as his and revealed that it would be released the following Thursday at midnight, on Friday, April 3, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-YkmtuFfCA/|title=THURSDAY @ MIDNIGHT @toosie @ozmusiqe|via=[[Instagram]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/drake-toosie-slide-tiktok-dance/|title=Drake's New Track \"Toosie Slide\" Drops This Thursday|last=Osei|first=Sarah|website=[[Highsnobiety]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> Fellow American rapper [[Lil Baby]] revealed via Instagram that Drake wanted him on the song, calling himself a \"dumbass\" for not sending his verse back.<ref name=\"Lil Baby\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/lil-baby-says-drake-wanted-him-on-toosie-slide|title=Lil Baby Says Drake Wanted Him on \"Toosie Slide\": 'My Dumb Ass Ain't Send the Verse'|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=Mahadevan|first=Tara|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nThe song was produced by Swiss producer Ozan Yildirim, professionally known as\u00a0[[OZ (record producer)|OZ]], who previously collaborated with [[Travis Scott]] on 2018's \"[[Sicko Mode]]\", featuring Drake. In 2019, he again worked with Drake on the songs [[The Best in the World Pack|\"Omert\u00e0\"]] and \"[[Gold Roses]]\", the latter being a [[Rick Ross]] single, featuring Drake. Just prior to \"Toosie Slide\", OZ produced another Drake-featured track, [[Future (rapper)|Future]]'s [[Life Is Good (song)|\"Life Is Good]]\". As with most of his productions, OZ makes extensive use of [[hi-hat]]s and a [[snare drum]] on \"Toosie Slide\". The song also contains [[bass drum]] kicks paired with Drake's \"melodic\" chorus.<ref name=\"5 Big\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide-5-big-takeaways|title=5 Big Takeaways From Drake's New Song \"Toosie Slide\"|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last1=Skelton|first1=Eric|last2=McKinney|first2=Jessica|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition and lyrics==\nA [[trap music|trap]] song,<ref name=\"COS\">{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide-stream/|title=Drake Invented a TikTok Dance with New Song \"Toosie Slide\" and Video: Stream|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|last=Corcoran|first=Nina|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> \"Toosie Slide\" is a \"seductive confection engineered to cause an Internet stir\",<ref name=\"NPR\" /> containing \"stuttering [[cymbal]]s, a couple [[bass drum]] kicks\" and \"elliptical set of beats\", leaving room for Drake's lyrics to take the spotlight,<ref name=\"COS\" /> which he delivers with \"melodic bars\".<ref name=\"5 Big\" /><ref name=\"Complex Best\" /> Lyrically, Drake reflects on his \"inner pressure\", shouting out his friends, flirting with his many admirers and promising \"a hot summer of music\".<ref name=\"First Stream\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9350420/first-stream-drake-sam-hunt-lindsay-lohan|title=First Stream: New Music From Drake, Sam Hunt, Lindsay Lohan & More|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|date=April 4, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> He also gives dance directions for the song's titular dance, rapping \"It go right foot up, left foot slide/Left foot up, right foot slide/Basically I'm saying, either way we 'bout to slide, aye\".<ref name=\"XXL\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide-song/|title=Drake Drops New Song \"Toosie Slide\": Listen|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|last=Johnson|first=Zoe|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> Drake makes numerous references to [[Michael Jackson]] throughout the song. \nDrake said, \"When I first made that song, I was only talking about the [[moonwalk (dance)|moonwalk]]. But Toosie made a dance to that shit, I didn't know it was gonna be a dance song like that\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cheatsheet.com/entertainment/drakes-toosie-slide-is-literally-just-a-moonwalk-tutorial-and-youve-been-doing-it-all-wrong.html/|title=Drake' Toosie Slide Is Literally Just A Moonwalk Tutorial And You've Been Doing It All Wrong|website=Cheat Sheet|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\nThe song has been compared to \"[[Cupid Shuffle]]\" by [[Cupid (singer)|Cupid]],<ref name=\"NPR\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2020/04/03/826808452/drake-quarantined-in-style-makes-private-isolation-a-public-spectacle|title=Drake, Quarantined In Style, Makes Social Isolation A Public Spectacle|website=[[NPR Music|NPR]]|author=[[Ann Powers|Powers, Ann]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> the [[Electric Slide]] dance by Richard L. \"Ric\" Silver,<ref name=\"Vice\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/y3m9nw/drake-bored-toosie-slide-tik-tok|title=Drake's Video for 'Toosie Slide' Proves He's Just As Bored as the Rest of Us|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|last=Rodrigues|first=Ashwin|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> and \"[[Cha Cha Slide]]\" by [[DJ Casper]], which has similar dance instructions.<ref name=\"forbes\" /> [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] called it the \"'Cha Cha Slide' of the [[TikTok]] generation\".<ref name=\"First Stream\" />\n\n==Critical reception==\n\"Toosie Slide\" generally polarized critics. Alphonse Pierre of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' noted that despite Drake's ability of never needing \"to chase a hit\", for the first time it \"feels like he's a step behind\" and went on calling the track \"strictly a business decision\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/drake-toosie-slide/|title=Drake \"Toosie Slide\"|last=Pierre|first=Alphonse|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> Micah Peters of [[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] was highly critical of the song as well as Drake's marketing ploys, comparing him to the [[DC Comics]] supervillian [[Darkseid]]. Peters further called producer [[OZ (record producer)|OZ]]'s production \"airy, barely there\", the [[hook (music)|hook]] \"awkward syllabic balance\" and said \"Toosie Slide\" feels marginal in the same way \"[[God's Plan (song)|God's Plan]]\" did, \"and doubtlessly, it'll also walk to no. 1\".<ref name=\"Ringer\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theringer.com/platform/music/2020/4/3/21207204/drake-toosie-slide-tiktok-dance-challenge|title=Drake's \"Toosie Slide\" Is a Master Class in Marketing, but Nothing Else|website=[[The Ringer (website)|Tye Ringer]]|last=Peters|first=Micah|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> [[Ann Powers]] of [[NPR Music|NPR]] had a similar notion, labelling the song \"a bit of trivial fun that will probably become an inescapable hit on the strength of its marketing and its catchy chorus\".<ref name=\"NPR\" /> Conversely, Jason Lipshutz of [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] named it among the most essential releases of the week, and said \"Drake is smart to launch a self-fashioned dance craze in this era, but 'Toosie Slide' also showcases his skill of conjuring hooks and catchphrases out of thin air, which helped make him who he is today\".<ref name=\"First Stream\"/> Jessica McKinney of [[Complex (magazine)|''Complex'']] also listed it as part of the \"Best New Music of the Week\", saying the song is not all gimmick and referenced the ongoing [[Coronavirus pandemic]], stating \"it is worth listening to when you're riding around in the car or heading out for a quick walk around the block. Maybe someday we'll actually get to hear it in a club\".<ref name=\"Complex Best\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/best-new-music-this-week-drake-dababy-rod-wave|title=Best New Music This Week: Drake, DaBaby, Rod Wave, and More|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=McKinney|first=Jessica|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nThe song debuted atop the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] on the chart dated April 18, 2020, making Drake the first male solo artist in US chart history to debut three songs at number one.<ref name=\"TS BB\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9357012/drake-toosie-slide-number-one-hot-100-debut|title=Drake Makes Historic Debut at No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100 With 'Toosie Slide'|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe accompanying music video was released on April 3, 2020, at a length of 5 minutes and 12 seconds. It was directed by Theo Skudra. The visuals prominently feature Drake dancing around in his [[Toronto]] mansion, nicknamed \"The Embassy\",<ref name=\"Rap Up\" /> with a mask and gloves on while being in quarantine, due to the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/listen-to-drakes-new-song-toosie-slide|title=Drake Shares Video for New Song \"Toosie Slide\" Watch|last=Bloom|first=Madison|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide-song/|title=Drake Drops New Song \"Toosie Slide\": Listen|last=Johnson|first=Zoe|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> He simultaneously demonstrates the song's titular dance. At the end, the rapper is seen outside of his home with a firework show on his property.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hypebeast.com/2020/4/drake-toosie-slide-music-video-single-stream|title=Drake Offers a House Tour For His \"Toosie Slide\" Music Video|last=Li|first=Nicolaus|website=Hypebeast|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> The video also features a tribute to the late [[Kobe Bryant]].<ref name=\"complex\"/> The choreography in the video was created by Toosie, Hiii Key and [[Ayo & Teo]] who sent the footage to Drake.<ref name=\"rollingstone\"/> Originally, the dancers were supposed to appear in the video. However, plans were scrapped due to the coronavirus pandemic.<ref name=\"complex\">{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide|title=Watch Drake's Video for New Single \"Toosie Slide\"|last=Espinoza|first=Joshua|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Synopsis===\nThe music video begins by showing quiet and almost deserted streets of the city, with no sign of cars, nor people moving around. The empty streets signify the quietness of the cities in the light of the lockdowns that have been enforced by governments globally to curb the spread of the Covid-19 virus among citizens. The video then shows Drake in a [[antechamber]], showcasing his many awards sitting in trophy cases; through the door, a painting of China's [[Mao Zedong|Chairman Mao]] by [[Andy Warhol]] is seen hanging on the wall. Drake then passes by a table covered with the\u00a0basketball jerseys\u00a0he is usually seen wearing courtside, including one emblazoned with the name \"Bryant\", honoring the late American basketball star, Kobe Bryant, who had died earlier the year from a [[Kobe Bryant death|helicopter crash]], on January 26, 2020. The scene then cuts to a foyer, as the rapper passes two sculptures by Japanese [[contemporary artist]] [[Takashi Murakami]]. The rapper is then seen sitting on \"the biggest kitchen island [...]\"\u00a0and the camera pans toward the quarter-mile-long dining room table. Drake continues moving through darkened rooms where portraits of \"lost and distanced\" heroes, including [[Prince (musician)|Prince]], [[Nas]], [[Tupac]] and [[Snoop Dogg]], hang on the wall. He dances through a door to the pool area,\u00a0which features \"waneon lighting and cabana-like d\u00e9cor\". The video concludes with Drake in total darkness, \"only his white sneakers visible against the eerily black [[Toronto]] sky\". Fireworks erupt afterward, and the camera pans back to show the entirety of Drake's 35,000-square-foot, $100 million Toronto estate.\n\nIn the video, Drake is seen wearing a hoodie and a \"super rare\" Fall/Winter 2001 [[Raf Simons]] Riot Riot Riot Camo [[Flight jacket#The bomber jacket|Bomber]], an item [[Kanye West]] wore regularly during 2014 and 2015. A [[B\u00f6sendorfer]] piano is seen, which has a violet cover inscribed with skulls.\u00a0There's also a shot of what appears to be a recording contract,\u00a0ready to be signed on Drake's dining-room table.\n\nSources:<ref name=\"NPR\" /><ref name=\"Missed Video\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/9350688/drake-toosie-slide-video-what-you-missed|title=7 Things You Might Have Missed Inside Drake's House in 'Toosie Slide' Video|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Saponara|first=Michael|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Rap Up\" />\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/136183311/credits|title=Drake / Toosie Slide / Tidal|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n* [[Drake (rapper)|Aubrey Graham]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter, composer\n* Nick Kobe - songwriter\n* [[OZ (record producer)|Ozan Yildirim]] \u2013 songwriter, composer, production\n* [[40 (record producer)|Noah \"40\" Shebib]] \u2013 mixer\n* Noel Cadastre \u2013 assistant mixer, recording engineer\n* Chris Athens \u2013 mastering engineer\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|2|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|8|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|35|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|3|artist=Drake|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|5|year=2020|week=16|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=15&y=2020&list=t40|title=Track Top-40 Uge 15, 2020|publisher=[[Hitlisten]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Estonia ([[Eesti Tipp-40]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ekspress.delfi.ee/areen/eesti-tipp-40-muusikas-sel-nadalal-paugutab-tradattack?id=89544845|title=EESTI TIPP-40 MUUSIKAS: Sel n\u00e4dalal paugutab Trad.Attack!|website=[[Eesti Ekspress]]|language=Estonian|access-date=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n{{single chart|Finland|4|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-semaine/top-albums/?semaine=16?&annee=2020&categorie=Top%20Singles|title=Top Singles (Week 16, 2020)|publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique]]|language=French|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany2|3|songid=1977918|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Greece ([[IFPI Greece|IFPI]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.gr/digital_ien.html|publisher=[[IFPI Greece]]|accessdate=April 14, 2020|title=Official IFPI Charts \u2013 Digital Singles Chart (International) \u2013 Week: 14/2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarysingle|28|year=2020|week=15|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarystream|4|year=2020|week=15|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Iceland ([[Music of Iceland|Tonlist]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://plotutidindi.is/lagalistinn/|title=T\u00d3NLISTINN \u2013 Vika 15 \u2013 2020; Pl\u00f6tut\u00ed\u00f0indi}}</ref>\n| 13\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland4|2|date=20200410|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italy ([[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fimi.it/top-of-the-music/classifiche.kl#/charts/3/2020/16|title=Top Singoli \u2013 Classifica settimanale WK 16|publisher=[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana]]|language=Italian|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Latvia ([[Latvijas Radio 5|Latvijas Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pieci.lv/lv/lr5/top40|title=Latvijas Top 40|publisher=[[Latvijas Radio]]|date=April 16, 2020|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| 23\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Lithuania ([[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.agata.lt/lt/naujienos/savaites-klausomiausi-2020w15/|title=2020 15-os SAVAIT\u0116S (baland\u017eio 3-9 d.) SINGL\u0172 TOP100|language=Lithuanian|publisher=[[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]]|date=April 10, 2020|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Malaysia ([[Recording Industry Association of Malaysia|RIM]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/RecordingIndustryMalaysia/photos/pcb.3393904137303599/3393903853970294/?type=3&theater|title=Top 20 Most Streamed International & Domestic Singles In Malaysia|work=[[Recording Industry Association of Malaysia]]|publisher=Recording Industry Association of Malaysia|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n| 8\n|-\n{{single chart|Dutch100|2|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand ([[Recorded Music NZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=4848|title=NZ Top 40 Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Norway ([[VG-lista]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vglista.no/topplister/topp-20-single-2020-16/|title=VG-lista \u2013 Topp 20 Single uke 16, 2020|publisher=[[VG-lista]]|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n| 4\n|-\n{{single chart|Scotland|13|date=20200417|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Singapore ([[Recording Industry Association (Singapore)|RIAS]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rias.org.sg/rias-top-charts/|title=RIAS International Top Charts Week 16|publisher=Recording Industry Association (Singapore)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200423081946/https://www.rias.org.sg/rias-top-charts/|archive-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{single chart|Slovakdigital|5|year=2020|week=16|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elportaldemusica.es/lists/top-100-canciones/2020/16|title=Top 100 Canciones: Semana 16|publisher=[[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a]]|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n| 39\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Sweden ([[Sverigetopplistan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/41?dspy=2020&dspp=16|title=Veckolista Singlar, vecka 16|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n{{single chart|Switzerland|2|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|2|date=20200410|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardhot100|1|artist=Drake|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardrandbhiphop|1|artist=Drake|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardpopsongs|16|artist=Drake|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardrhythmic|7|artist=Drake|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! Country\n! Date\n! Format\n! Label\n! {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| April 3, 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| {{hlist|[[Republic Records|Republic]]|[[OVO Sound|OVO]]}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/toosie-slide-single/1505950451|title=Toosie Slide - Single by Drake on Apple Music|via=[[Apple Music]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| April 7, 2020\n| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| {{hlist|[[Cash Money Records|Cash Money]]|[[Young Money Entertainment|Young Money]]|[[Republic Records|Republic]]}}\n| <ref name=\"AllAccess\">{{cite web|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|website=All Access|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330200214/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archivedate=March 31, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*\"[[Nonstop (song)|Nonstop]]\", a 2018 song by Drake which also went viral on TikTok in 2018 and again in 2020\n*[[List of number-one hits of 2020 (Denmark)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles from the 2020s (New Zealand)#2020|List of number-one singles from the 2020s (New Zealand)]]\n*[[List of number-one songs of 2020 (Singapore)]]\n*[[List of Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles of 2020|List of ''Billboard'' Hot 100 number-one singles of 2020]]\n*[[List of Billboard Hot 100 top-ten singles in 2020|List of ''Billboard'' Hot 100 top-ten singles in 2020]]\n*[[List of number-one Billboard Streaming Songs of 2020|List of number-one ''Billboard'' Streaming Songs of 2020]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Drake songs}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Drake (musician) songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Drake (musician)]]\n[[Category:Republic Records singles]]\n[[Category:Trap music songs]]\n[[Category:TikTok songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 song by Drake}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Toosie Slide\n| cover      = Drake - Toosie Slide.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2020|4|3|mf=y}}\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres --> [[trap music|Trap]]<ref name=\"COS\" />\n| length     = {{duration|m=4|s=7}}\n| label      =\n* [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n* [[OVO Sound|OVO]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Drake (musician)|Aubrey Graham]]\n* Nick Kobe\n* [[OZ (record producer)|Ozan Yildirim]]\n| producer   = [[OZ (record producer)|OZ]]\n| prev_title = [[Oprah's Bank Account]]\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|xWggTb45brM|\"Toosie Slide\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Toosie Slide'''\" is a song by Canadian rapper [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]. It was released on April 3, 2020, through [[Republic Records|Republic]] and [[OVO Sound|OVO]].<ref name=\"forbes\"/> The song is titled after social media influencer Toosie who had previously helped the song go viral.<ref name=\"Rap Up\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2020/04/02/new-music-drake-toosie-slide/|title=Drake Returns With New Single \"Toosie Slide\"|work=[[Rap-Up]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> A video was released alongside the song, showing Drake [[quarantined]], due to the ongoing [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]]. He is seen on the video wearing a mask and a pair of gloves to signify the safety precautions that have been taken globally to curb the spread of the virus. He also demonstrates the Toosie Slide dance in his [[Toronto]] mansion. The song debuted at number one on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart, making Drake the first male artist to accomplish three number-one debuts.<ref name=\"TS BB\"/>\n\n==Background and promotion==\nOn March 29, 2020, social media influencer Toosie uploaded a clip showing him and his friends doing a dance challenge called the \"Toosie Slide\" while parts of the song are playing in the background.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/03/drake-unreleased-toosie-slide-snippet-tiktok|title=Drake Could Be Primed for TikTok Domination After Snippet From Unreleased Song Inspires \"Toosie Slide\" (UPDATE)|last=Martinez|first=Jose|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/unclick/drake-toosie-slide-tiktok/|title=Reportedly unreleased Drake track leads to viral TikTok dance|last=Schroeder|first=Audra|work=[[Daily Dot]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> The dance was described as a \"modern day '[[Cha Cha Slide]]' by [[DJ Casper]]\" and went viral after it was introduced to the app [[TikTok]] by Toosie, Hiii Key and Michigan duo [[Ayo & Teo]].<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/laurenalvarez/2020/03/31/drake-announces-new-single-toosie-slide-coming-thursday-night/#761fe0c279fd|title=Drake Announces New Single \"Toosie Slide\" Coming Thursday Night|last=Alvarez|first=Lauren|work=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"rollingstone\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/drake-toosie-slide-song-977734/|title=Drake Grooves Down Empty Street and Mansion in Video for \"Toosie Slide\"|last=Legaspi|first=Althea|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> When it was subsequently shared on other social media pages, people considered possible involvement by Drake.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hiphop-n-more.com/2020/03/new-drake-song-tik-tok-toosie-slide/|title=Drake Previews New Tik Tok-Type Song for \"Toosie Slide\": Listen|author=Navjosh|website=HipHopNMore|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> He hinted at an impending release, saying \"I'mma drop soon since ya'll got it going insane\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/drake-promises-to-drop-newly-teased-song-news.107507.html|title=Drake Promises To Drop Newly Teased Song|last=A.|first=Aron|website=[[HotNewHipHop]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> Drake then took to his social media on March 31, 2020, to declare the song as his and revealed that it would be released the following Thursday at midnight, on Friday, April 3, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-YkmtuFfCA/|title=THURSDAY @ MIDNIGHT @toosie @ozmusiqe|via=[[Instagram]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/drake-toosie-slide-tiktok-dance/|title=Drake's New Track \"Toosie Slide\" Drops This Thursday|last=Osei|first=Sarah|website=[[Highsnobiety]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref> Fellow American rapper [[Lil Baby]] revealed via Instagram that Drake wanted him on the song, calling himself a \"dumbass\" for not sending his verse back.<ref name=\"Lil Baby\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/lil-baby-says-drake-wanted-him-on-toosie-slide|title=Lil Baby Says Drake Wanted Him on \"Toosie Slide\": 'My Dumb Ass Ain't Send the Verse'|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=Mahadevan|first=Tara|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nThe song was produced by Swiss producer Ozan Yildirim, professionally known as\u00a0[[OZ (record producer)|OZ]], who previously collaborated with [[Travis Scott]] on 2018's \"[[Sicko Mode]]\", featuring Drake. In 2019, he again worked with Drake on the songs [[The Best in the World Pack|\"Omert\u00e0\"]] and \"[[Gold Roses]]\", the latter being a [[Rick Ross]] single, featuring Drake. Just prior to \"Toosie Slide\", OZ produced another Drake-featured track, [[Future (rapper)|Future]]'s [[Life Is Good (song)|\"Life Is Good]]\". As with most of his productions, OZ makes extensive use of [[hi-hat]]s and a [[snare drum]] on \"Toosie Slide\". The song also contains [[bass drum]] kicks paired with Drake's \"melodic\" chorus.<ref name=\"5 Big\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide-5-big-takeaways|title=5 Big Takeaways From Drake's New Song \"Toosie Slide\"|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last1=Skelton|first1=Eric|last2=McKinney|first2=Jessica|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition and lyrics==\nA [[trap music|trap]] song,<ref name=\"COS\">{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide-stream/|title=Drake Invented a TikTok Dance with New Song \"Toosie Slide\" and Video: Stream|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|last=Corcoran|first=Nina|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> \"Toosie Slide\" is a \"seductive confection engineered to cause an Internet stir\",<ref name=\"NPR\" /> containing \"stuttering [[cymbal]]s, a couple [[bass drum]] kicks\" and \"elliptical set of beats\", leaving room for Drake's lyrics to take the spotlight,<ref name=\"COS\" /> which he delivers with \"melodic bars\".<ref name=\"5 Big\" /><ref name=\"Complex Best\" /> Lyrically, Drake reflects on his \"inner pressure\", shouting out his friends, flirting with his many admirers and promising \"a hot summer of music\".<ref name=\"First Stream\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9350420/first-stream-drake-sam-hunt-lindsay-lohan|title=First Stream: New Music From Drake, Sam Hunt, Lindsay Lohan & More|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|date=April 4, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> He also gives dance directions for the song's titular dance, rapping \"It go right foot up, left foot slide/Left foot up, right foot slide/Basically I'm saying, either way we 'bout to slide, aye\".<ref name=\"XXL\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide-song/|title=Drake Drops New Song \"Toosie Slide\": Listen|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|last=Johnson|first=Zoe|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> Drake makes numerous references to [[Michael Jackson]] throughout the song. \nDrake said, \"When I first made that song, I was only talking about the [[moonwalk (dance)|moonwalk]]. But Toosie made a dance to that shit, I didn't know it was gonna be a dance song like that\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cheatsheet.com/entertainment/drakes-toosie-slide-is-literally-just-a-moonwalk-tutorial-and-youve-been-doing-it-all-wrong.html/|title=Drake' Toosie Slide Is Literally Just A Moonwalk Tutorial And You've Been Doing It All Wrong|website=Cheat Sheet|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\nThe song has been compared to \"[[Cupid Shuffle]]\" by [[Cupid (singer)|Cupid]],<ref name=\"NPR\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2020/04/03/826808452/drake-quarantined-in-style-makes-private-isolation-a-public-spectacle|title=Drake, Quarantined In Style, Makes Social Isolation A Public Spectacle|website=[[NPR Music|NPR]]|author=[[Ann Powers|Powers, Ann]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> the [[Electric Slide]] dance by Richard L. \"Ric\" Silver,<ref name=\"Vice\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/y3m9nw/drake-bored-toosie-slide-tik-tok|title=Drake's Video for 'Toosie Slide' Proves He's Just As Bored as the Rest of Us|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|last=Rodrigues|first=Ashwin|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> and \"[[Cha Cha Slide]]\" by [[DJ Casper]], which has similar dance instructions.<ref name=\"forbes\" /> [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] called it the \"'Cha Cha Slide' of the [[TikTok]] generation\".<ref name=\"First Stream\" />\n\n==Critical reception==\n\"Toosie Slide\" generally polarized critics. Alphonse Pierre of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' noted that despite Drake's ability of never needing \"to chase a hit\", for the first time it \"feels like he's a step behind\" and went on calling the track \"strictly a business decision\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/drake-toosie-slide/|title=Drake \"Toosie Slide\"|last=Pierre|first=Alphonse|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> Micah Peters of [[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] was highly critical of the song as well as Drake's marketing ploys, comparing him to the [[DC Comics]] supervillian [[Darkseid]]. Peters further called producer [[OZ (record producer)|OZ]]'s production \"airy, barely there\", the [[hook (music)|hook]] \"awkward syllabic balance\" and said \"Toosie Slide\" feels marginal in the same way \"[[God's Plan (song)|God's Plan]]\" did, \"and doubtlessly, it'll also walk to no. 1\".<ref name=\"Ringer\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theringer.com/platform/music/2020/4/3/21207204/drake-toosie-slide-tiktok-dance-challenge|title=Drake's \"Toosie Slide\" Is a Master Class in Marketing, but Nothing Else|website=[[The Ringer (website)|Tye Ringer]]|last=Peters|first=Micah|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> [[Ann Powers]] of [[NPR Music|NPR]] had a similar notion, labelling the song \"a bit of trivial fun that will probably become an inescapable hit on the strength of its marketing and its catchy chorus\".<ref name=\"NPR\" /> Conversely, Jason Lipshutz of [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] named it among the most essential releases of the week, and said \"Drake is smart to launch a self-fashioned dance craze in this era, but 'Toosie Slide' also showcases his skill of conjuring hooks and catchphrases out of thin air, which helped make him who he is today\".<ref name=\"First Stream\"/> Jessica McKinney of [[Complex (magazine)|''Complex'']] also listed it as part of the \"Best New Music of the Week\", saying the song is not all gimmick and referenced the ongoing [[Coronavirus pandemic]], stating \"it is worth listening to when you're riding around in the car or heading out for a quick walk around the block. Maybe someday we'll actually get to hear it in a club\".<ref name=\"Complex Best\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/best-new-music-this-week-drake-dababy-rod-wave|title=Best New Music This Week: Drake, DaBaby, Rod Wave, and More|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=McKinney|first=Jessica|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nThe song debuted atop the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] on the chart dated April 18, 2020, making Drake the first male solo artist in US chart history to debut three songs at number one.<ref name=\"TS BB\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9357012/drake-toosie-slide-number-one-hot-100-debut|title=Drake Makes Historic Debut at No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100 With 'Toosie Slide'|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe accompanying music video was released on April 3, 2020, at a length of 5 minutes and 12 seconds. It was directed by Theo Skudra. The visuals prominently feature Drake dancing around in his [[Toronto]] mansion, nicknamed \"The Embassy\",<ref name=\"Rap Up\" /> with a mask and gloves on while being in quarantine, due to the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/listen-to-drakes-new-song-toosie-slide|title=Drake Shares Video for New Song \"Toosie Slide\" Watch|last=Bloom|first=Madison|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide-song/|title=Drake Drops New Song \"Toosie Slide\": Listen|last=Johnson|first=Zoe|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> He simultaneously demonstrates the song's titular dance. At the end, the rapper is seen outside of his home with a firework show on his property.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hypebeast.com/2020/4/drake-toosie-slide-music-video-single-stream|title=Drake Offers a House Tour For His \"Toosie Slide\" Music Video|last=Li|first=Nicolaus|website=Hypebeast|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> The video also features a tribute to the late [[Kobe Bryant]].<ref name=\"complex\"/> The choreography in the video was created by Toosie, Hiii Key and [[Ayo & Teo]] who sent the footage to Drake.<ref name=\"rollingstone\"/> Originally, the dancers were supposed to appear in the video. However, plans were scrapped due to the coronavirus pandemic.<ref name=\"complex\">{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/drake-toosie-slide|title=Watch Drake's Video for New Single \"Toosie Slide\"|last=Espinoza|first=Joshua|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Synopsis===\nThe music video begins by showing quiet and almost deserted streets of the city, with no sign of cars, nor people moving around. The empty streets signify the quietness of the cities in the light of the lockdowns that have been enforced by governments globally to curb the spread of the Covid-19 virus among citizens. The video then shows Drake in a [[antechamber]], showcasing his many awards sitting in trophy cases; through the door, a painting of China's [[Mao Zedong|Chairman Mao]] by [[Andy Warhol]] is seen hanging on the wall. Drake then passes by a table covered with the\u00a0basketball jerseys\u00a0he is usually seen wearing courtside, including one emblazoned with the name \"Bryant\", honoring the late American basketball star, Kobe Bryant, who had died earlier the year from a [[Kobe Bryant death|helicopter crash]], on January 26, 2020. The scene then cuts to a foyer, as the rapper passes two sculptures by Japanese [[contemporary artist]] [[Takashi Murakami]]. The rapper is then seen sitting on \"the biggest kitchen island [...]\"\u00a0and the camera pans toward the quarter-mile-long dining room table. Drake continues moving through darkened rooms where portraits of \"lost and distanced\" heroes, including [[Prince (musician)|Prince]], [[Nas]], [[Tupac]] and [[Snoop Dogg]], hang on the wall. He dances through a door to the pool area,\u00a0which features \"waneon lighting and cabana-like d\u00e9cor\". The video concludes with Drake in total darkness, \"only his white sneakers visible against the eerily black [[Toronto]] sky\". Fireworks erupt afterward, and the camera pans back to show the entirety of Drake's 35,000-square-foot, $100 million Toronto estate.\n\nIn the video, Drake is seen wearing a hoodie and a \"super rare\" Fall/Winter 2001 [[Raf Simons]] Riot Riot Riot Camo [[Flight jacket#The bomber jacket|Bomber]], an item [[Kanye West]] wore regularly during 2014 and 2015. A [[B\u00f6sendorfer]] piano is seen, which has a violet cover inscribed with skulls.\u00a0There's also a shot of what appears to be a recording contract,\u00a0ready to be signed on Drake's dining-room table.\n\nSources:<ref name=\"NPR\" /><ref name=\"Missed Video\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/9350688/drake-toosie-slide-video-what-you-missed|title=7 Things You Might Have Missed Inside Drake's House in 'Toosie Slide' Video|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Saponara|first=Michael|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Rap Up\" />\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/136183311/credits|title=Drake / Toosie Slide / Tidal|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n* [[Drake (rapper)|Aubrey Graham]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter, composer\n* Nick Kobe - songwriter\n* [[OZ (record producer)|Ozan Yildirim]] \u2013 songwriter, composer, production\n* [[40 (record producer)|Noah \"40\" Shebib]] \u2013 mixer\n* Noel Cadastre \u2013 assistant mixer, recording engineer\n* Chris Athens \u2013 mastering engineer\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|2|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|8|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|35|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|3|artist=Drake|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|5|year=2020|week=16|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=15&y=2020&list=t40|title=Track Top-40 Uge 15, 2020|publisher=[[Hitlisten]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Estonia ([[Eesti Tipp-40]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ekspress.delfi.ee/areen/eesti-tipp-40-muusikas-sel-nadalal-paugutab-tradattack?id=89544845|title=EESTI TIPP-40 MUUSIKAS: Sel n\u00e4dalal paugutab Trad.Attack!|website=[[Eesti Ekspress]]|language=Estonian|access-date=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n{{single chart|Finland|4|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-semaine/top-albums/?semaine=16?&annee=2020&categorie=Top%20Singles|title=Top Singles (Week 16, 2020)|publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique]]|language=French|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany2|3|songid=1977918|artist=Drake|song=Toosie Slide|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Greece ([[IFPI Greece|IFPI]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.gr/digital_ien.html|publisher=[[IFPI Greece]]|accessdate=April 14, 2020|title=Official IFPI Charts \u2013 Digital Singles Chart (International) \u2013 Week: 14/2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarysingle|28|year=2020|week=15|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarystream|4|year=2020|week=15|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Iceland ([[Music of Iceland|Tonlist]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://plotutidindi.is/lagalistinn/|title=T\u00d3NLISTINN \u2013 Vika 15 \u2013 2020; Pl\u00f6tut\u00ed\u00f0indi}}</ref>\n| 13\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland4|2|date=20200410|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italy ([[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fimi.it/top-of-the-music/classifiche.kl#/charts/3/2020/16|title=Top Singoli \u2013 Classifica settimanale WK 16|publisher=[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana]]|language=Italian|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Latvia ([[Latvijas Radio 5|Latvijas Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http: